 there and thank you to all that sent tells this weekend.  Oh and the Kirak Vil protion has been cancelled as a team of CS members helped me attain victory against him this weekend.  WOOT! <br>
<br>
Copy of Message on CS Boards:<br>
<br>
ATTENTION!  ATTENTION!  Greetings all and I hope this message meets you all in good spirts and good health.  I have done something that I would usually not do, but in order to attempt to complete the next part of my epic would like to change the date and time of this event to March 29th and 3:00 pm PST.<br>
<br>
The reason for this change is due to the PoA raid being cancelled this past weekend and rescheduled to April 5th. I was given permission by Hart (Thank you milady! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->          ) to piggy back my hand-in on the pegasus island to complete my 3rd epic blade quest if I am able to slay Miragul for my final 2 pieces needed to attain my Fiery Avenger.<br>
<br>
Miragul is a 53rd level necromancer that is said to be tough but slayable by a strong single group though I would like to have at least 3 groups to make sure that success is guaranteed.  We will need a 60th level enchanter to charm (NO mezzes) the Lich of Miragul in order to get Miragul to spawn but the rest of the classes that can attend is open.  I have access to a level 60 enchanter that I can play on a second computer, but have no idea of even what spell I use to charm a level 53 mob...silly paladin. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->            Any advice would be appreciated.  I will attach a few links to sites related to this quest and mobs below.<br>
<br>
Quest for Fiery Avenger:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=10">everquest.allakhazam.com/...l?quest=10</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Lich of Miragul:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=3558">eqbeastiary.allakhazam.co...ml?id=3558</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Miragul (true form):<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=3688">eqbeastiary.allakhazam.co...ml?id=3688</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Maps of Everfrost &amp; the caves:<br>
Everfrost: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eqatlas.com/everfrostmap.html">eqatlas.com/everfrostmap.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Caves:  <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eqatlas.com/everfrostcavesmap.html">eqatlas.com/everfrostcavesmap.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
I thank anyone that can help with this epic battle and apologize for changing the date and time, but opportunities to go to PoA with a group such as Forsaken Fellowship do not come around everyday.<br>
<br>
P.S.  This battle should be relatively quick once we get organized into groups and into the caves in Everfrost.  After the battle has been won I have heard that it is a good idea to get everyone to Nektulos Forest to see if Kirak Vil is up.  He is a level 56 guard that is a 7 to 10 day spawn...what is new for a paladin epic mob. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->            If he is up and wandering around it is said that the Miragul adventures make an excellent team to slay this fiend.  Kirak is tough to root, has a high magic resistance, but is slowable and very slayable for such a team.  A link about Kirak is below.<br>
<br>
Kirak Vil:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=5172">eqbeastiary.allakhazam.co...ml?id=5172</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
<br>
